-- Central Bank Sells 3-Month Bills at Unchanged 1.5704% Yield, Traders Say
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-29T02:08:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/central-bank-sells-3-month-bills-at-unchanged-1-5704-yield-traders-say.html

          
          
             The Peopleâ€™s Bank of China sold
three-month bills at a yield of 1.5704 percent in open-market
operations, unchanged for the fifth straight sale, according to
traders at BOC International (China) Ltd. and China Citic Bank
Corp.  
 The monetary authority, which offered 22 billion yuan ($3.2
billion) of the 91-day notes, has let the yield rise at five
previous auctions this year. The rate last climbed four basis
points, or 0.04 percentage point, to 1.5704 percent on June 10.  
